PredictiveViz

Interactive predictive model visualization

This code creates a visualization of predictive model using data from the ABIDE preprocessed functional MRI resting state dataset. The visualization is available at https://jcbeer.github.io/predictiveViz/.

The goal of the visualization is to illustrate how the predictive map and prediction accuracy change as a function of the alpha and lambda tuning parameters of the elastic net estimator.

This data was also used in this structured sparse regression methodology project.

The visualization is based on code from scatterize. You can upload a CSV file to scatterize here.

It also uses the Papaya medical image viewer, with code and documentation available here.
